<br>
The problem is that MOST of us are talking about teaming up on ONLY THREE mobs that are not rotation mobs.<br>
<br>
What you and a handful of others are doing is addressing a topic that is not part of the discussion.<br>
<br>
It seems logical, given the server's past that guilds will continue to respect rotations.  So if RZtW is on a ROTATION then people cannot kill him as an alliance without botching ALL of their rotations, thus they will not do it.<br>
<br>
You are acting like it is *not possible* to differentiate between mobs that are not currently on rotation with mobs that are.  You are also implying that guilds cooperating on NON rotation mobs could lead to guilds cooperating on ROTATION mobs, which would explicitly be against the rules.<br>
<br>
On one side we have people NOT breaking rules, and helping each other.  On the other hand there is BREAKING the rules and two guilds losing all of their rotations.  The two scenarios are QUITE different.<br>
<br>
So once more:<br>
<br>
1.  AD, Grummus, Behemoth are not currently rotation mobs.<br>
2.  By teaming on them, nobody has broken any rules.<br>
3.  Guilds may NOT team on rotations mobs without suffering the consequence of forming an alliance on rotations.<br>
<br>
I feel like that is easy enough for everyone to understand.  Drop the paranoia, or whatever it is that leads to your inability to &quot;trust&quot; people.  You have every right to worry about people breaking established rules, but that hasn't happened here.<br>
<br>
Here's a small comparision:  I can drive a car. I can also drive a car down a road where pedestrians cross frequently.  Just because pedestrians cross my path, doesn't mean I am going to run them over.  If I DO run them over, it is against the law, and I suffer consequences.<br>
<br>
Same thing here.  I can fight mobs.  I can fight non-rotation mobs with as many people, from as many guilds as I want.  Just because I team up on non-rotation mobs doesn't mean I will team up on rotation mobs.  If I team up on rotation mobs, I have broken the rules and will suffer the consequences.<br>
<br>
Once more:  What is the problem?<br>
<br>
