<br>
I think you are missing what I said.  I said the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>SPIRIT</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of the rotation system.  Since most people seem to be missing what that means let's use a few examples.<br>
<br>
BotS currently has a guild for both alts and friends called Baby Spiers.  Hypothetically speaking some of us don't all get along 100% and what not, so we have decided to make a number of smaller guilds.  These smaller guilds will house both alts of certain BotS members plus friends of those members.  The new guilds will be called the following:<br>
-Baby Spiders<br>
-Mini Spider<br>
-Junior Spiders<br>
-Lowbie Spiders<br>
-Teenage Mutant Ninja Spiders<br>
<br>
We will slowly be gearing up our friends in their respective guilds and would like 5 rotations on all mobs that they can kill.  We anicipate this to include but not be limited to the following:  Trak, AoW, KT, Sev, Greig, Dozekar, Cazic Thule, Zlandicar and Klandicar.  We anticipate them entering these rotations within the next cycle.<br>
<br>
See how ludicrous this becomes?  This violates the SPIRIT of the rotation system.  Although by the letter of the law it would not be violating the RTA rules, that does not make it any more valid.  That is the point here that I think most people are continually missing.  The point is you want to pick and choose when and where you start teaming up on boss mob encounters.  No one ever said you &quot;CAN'T&quot; team.  What they did say was fine team, but merge ALL you rotations when you decide to start teaming.  <br>
<br>
All this talk about holding people down is nothing more than wanting your cake and eating it too.  We want to get as much loot as we can, as many keys as we can, as many flags as we can for our guild no matter how we do it.  You talk about the greed of uber guilds wanting to hold mid to lower tier guilds down?  I argue the it is those same guilds wanting to ask guilds who on a whim could easily gank such targets to not do so.  Then on the other hand try to get into as much of that loot, keys flags as they can for themselves.  Perhpas here is a good illustration:<br>
<br>
Meduim Guild:<br>
They are a guild of about 50 hard core players who often have around 40 online at peak hours.<br>
<br>
They kill 3 mobs<br>
mob_A - this takes them about half their hardcore members to kill, they often have done it with as few as 4 groups or about 22 people.  They often know when he is up and could kill him pretty much upon respawn if they so choose to.  He has 2 decent loot drops that is currenlty working it's way through their lower ranks.<br>
mob_B - this takes them about 2/3 their hardcore members to kill, they often have done it with as few as 5 full groups or 30 people.  They usually know when he is up and could kill him pretty much upon a few hours of respawn if they so choose to.  He has 2 above average loots that are currently going to upper level and mid rank members.<br>
mob_C - This takes them all of their all to do.  He is an uber mob and has great loot, but they need 45+ people to turn out or they just can't do it.  They are fortunate to be able to kill this mob.  He drops excellent loot and only their top ranks are seeing it at this time.<br>
<br>
Small Medium Guild_01 (SMG1)<br>
They are a guild of about 30 hard core players.  Who often have around 25 members on at peak hours.  When raids are scheduled almsot all their hard core members are there as well as some of their more casual players.  Full raid force usually consists of about 40 at max.<br>
<br>
They Kill 2 mobs:<br>
mob_A. - This mob they have down pat now.  It used to take them all they could get online, but after a few times they really have a good strategy down.  They have often done it with as few as 25 at the raid.  They usually plan for this event and let all their members know when the upcoming spawn is to ensure that they have the numbers they need to kill him.  Currently loot is going to the top and mid level ranks in the guild.<br>
mob_B - This mob they are very fortunate to be able to kill.  Medium Guild above gave them a shot at it a few months ago.  They had all their hard core members on and most of their casual members.  They had a bulk raid force of 45 players for this raid and are in the rotation for it.  Currently all loot is goign to top end ranks in the guild only.<br>
mob_C - Well they have tried this mob a few times, but right now it is beyond them to able to do it because of numbers, levels and gear, but they hope to be able to kill him one day.<br>
<br>
Small Medium Guild_02 (SMG2)<br>
They are nearly identical to Small Medium Guild_01.  They are on the same rotations, and have the same aspirations of killing mob_C.  They also however suffer the same logistcal problems that they have serious difficulties dropping mob_B unless all their members know when he is spawning and they have all their hard core members there plus a good many of their more casual players there to ensure success.<br>
<br>
Small Medium Guild ( 01 and 02) decide to team up on mob_C and share the loot between them since they can't take him on alone yet, they know combined they could do it.  They decide to kill him as one entity for only mob_C and ask to remain seperate rotations on mobs A &amp; B.<br>
<br>
Please tell me you now don't see the hypocrisy of this?  The larger guild in theis scenario could easily be ganking mob_A everytime it spawned, and mob_B within a few hours of spawning.  HOWEVER they graciously decide to put their greedy ways aside and let BOTH Small Medium Guilds have a fair equal unhindered shot at those mobs.  The understanding is that these guilds won't abuse that goodwill.  Herein lies the abuse.  SMG 01 and 02 now want a rotation on mob_C, but seperate rotations on mobs A &amp; B.<br>
<br>
Honestly I can't see how this strikes anyone as fair, and I tihnk most would agree it is not fair.  Per rotation cycle they are getting 2 lower level loots, 2 medium type loots and 2 uber type loots.  They still have plenty of members who could use alot more of those 2 lower level and medium type loots.<br>
<br>
Here is the reason it is not fair:<br>
Quite frankly they would like to perma farm mob_A for about 2 or 3 months and be done with him.  However since they are fairly rotating this mob it will take them around 6-9 months to finish up with Mob_A and possibly 1-2 years to finish up with mob_B.  At the same time they are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>delaying their own progress</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, you are now asking them to further delay it to cater to both SMG's?  If both SMG's want to ally that is A-O-K, so long as they now merge their alliance on both mobs_A&amp;B as well.  In that way, although the larger guild is now also slowed down in their progression through mob C, at least they have speeded up their progression on mobs A &amp; B.<br>
<br>
Therein lies the *SPIRIT* of the system.  Larger guilds delay their progress on certain mobs so that all have a fair shot at it.  The *SPIRIT* is about progression.<br>
<br>
I would like to ask how far do you think teaming up on progression would be logical and fair?<br>
<br>
Quoting Roggulbuk who is Quoting Karadin<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Quote:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Let’s take your actions to their logical extreme: You guys successfully killed Aerin Dar, why stop there? I’ve been told you can xp in the Elemental Planes, so why not team up with VoLS to get t<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
<br>
Well, honestly, if you *can* xp grind in the elemental planes, and the mobs that flag you for those are not on rotation, nor justify a rotation by demand or loot, and there is an alternative quest that allows access to those zones, then I say 'why not?'<br>
<br>
We're not after loot from the mob we killed, just like was discussed. On a risk vs reward scale, Aerin Dar won't be something that we push for a rotation on. Our primary motivation for going to HoH is not loot, I believe you misunderstood my statement; Xedd made the claim that loot is easy to get there, I used that to suggest that it was not primarily a raiding zone.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That right there is what the heart of the issue is all about.  Everyone wants to draw the line at different places.  Some say AD, some think the Elemental planes.  So then what?  You team on all boss mobs up to Rallos Zek (RZ) because you are only &quot;after xp&quot;, to get past RZ to &quot;xp&quot; in the elemental planes and find that some min's there are actually not quite as hard as RZ.  Then some guilds decide hey our guild can kill said mini boss on our own, we want to rotate this mob and kill it on a regular basis.  I call foul!  The means by which you even accessed the content was one of teaming, however now you want 2 rotations on Blizzak because he is eaiser for you to do than RZ?  These guilds then start looking to the 3 other elemental planes as well?  <br>
<br>
Where should you draw the line to prevent it BEFORE it gets to this stage?  At the start of the whole road is the best place to raise such objections, rather than when faced with this exact scenario.  On other servers they have raids of 400 people to kill RZ.  There was a reason sony implemented the 72 flag rule.  I would much rather, and I am sure if you were honest you would to, that objections are raised at the start of this issue rather than half way through.  If not I can hear it already..... &quot;Well you didn't say anything when we killed AD so what is the big deal now?&quot;<br>
<br>
If no one believes in the *SPIRIT* of the rotations, IE only the letter of the law should apply, I am certain you will have no problems with members from BotS, Tindi, NB, etc... ganking 2 and 3 sxpansion old content on a whim.  They will hang their heads and take the shame of the community and skip this rot and the next rot as due punishment, for rots that they are not even on.  See the letter of the law is followed here as well, however I am sure it just doesn't seem fair when the shoe is on the other foot. <p>Soneya<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
Coercer<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
