<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Concerning Aerin Dar, Grummus, Behemoth:<br>
a) Because the mob the trigger for recieving 72 keys everytime to grant access to another zone,<br>
b) Because you can also quest a key to give access to this same other zone,<br>
c) Because the flag is the primary focus and the tangible items that the mob drops are of no primary consequence to anyone,<br>
d) As evidence of a), b), and c) there has been no contention for this mob as of yet as evidenced by the fact that this mob has been left alive for periods often greater than 72 hours,<br>
e) Then the mob doesn't require rotation and, therefore, no rules, which allow teaming up on the mob in any form desired.<br>
f) However, it may be in the future that a rotation needs to be in effect on this mob, if contention increases to the point some guild/group requests it.<br>
g) in distinction of item b), should this mob be placed on rotation, a further exemption will be set forth allowing an alliance of guilds to team up on this mob only for the purpose of receiving their flag; however, any further attempts on this mob for the purpose of additional flagging or for purposes of loot must be accomplished by that alliance as one rotation entity.<br>
h) following current alliance policy, any break up of an alliance will result in the alliance being removed from the rotation, and each guild must each kill the mob separately to be placed back on the rotation.<br>
<br>
Then, this can be similarly applied (or inherited if you like) by any other mob having similar properties in the future.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
